# Jetson Development Rules
# Connection command: ssh jetson@jetson
# This allows SSH access to the Jetson Nano for development and deployment

## Service Locations

### Local Development (macOS)
- Brain Server: ./services/brain-server/
- Signal Gateway: ./services/signal-gateway/
- Configs: ./services/openclaw-config/
- Scripts: ./scripts/

### Remote Deployment (Jetson)
- Brain Server binary: /home/jetson/brain-server/
- Signal Gateway binary: /home/jetson/signal-gateway/
- Systemd services: /etc/systemd/system/
- Configs: /etc/signal-gateway/

## Deployment Commands

### Brain Server
```bash
# 1. Build locally (cross-compile for ARM64)
cd services/brain-server
cargo build --release

# 2. Sync to Jetson
rsync -avz target/release/brain-server jetson@jetson:/home/jetson/brain-server/

# 3. Restart service on Jetson
ssh jetson@jetson "sudo systemctl restart brain-server"

# 4. Check status
ssh jetson@jetson "sudo systemctl status brain-server"
```

### Signal Gateway
```bash
# 1. Build locally (cross-compile for ARM64)
cd services/signal-gateway
cargo build --release

# 2. Sync to Jetson
rsync -avz target/release/signal-gateway jetson@jetson:/home/jetson/signal-gateway/

# 3. Sync wrapper script
rsync -avz scripts/signal-gateway-wrapper.sh jetson@jetson:/home/jetson/signal-gateway-wrapper.sh
ssh jetson@jetson "sudo cp /home/jetson/signal-gateway-wrapper.sh /usr/local/bin/ && sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/signal-gateway-wrapper.sh"

# 4. Restart service on Jetson
ssh jetson@jetson "sudo systemctl restart signal-gateway"

# 5. Check status
ssh jetson@jetson "sudo systemctl status signal-gateway"
```

### Full Sync (both services)
```bash
# Build both
./scripts/build-all.sh

# Sync both
rsync -avz services/brain-server/target/release/brain-server jetson@jetson:/home/jetson/
rsync -avz services/signal-gateway/target/release/signal-gateway jetson@jetson:/home/jetson/

# Restart both services
ssh jetson@jetson "sudo systemctl restart brain-server signal-gateway"
```

## Testing Endpoints

### Brain Server (Jetson)
- Health: ssh jetson@jetson "curl -s http://localhost:8765/health"
- Stats: ssh jetson@jetson "curl -s http://localhost:8765/stats | jq ."
- Search: ssh jetson@jetson "curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8765/search -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"query\": \"test\", \"k\": 5}' | jq ."
- Embeddings: ssh jetson@jetson "curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8765/v1/embeddings -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"input\": \"test\"}' | jq '.data[0].embedding | length'"

### Signal Gateway (Jetson)
- Health: ssh jetson@jetson "curl -s http://localhost:8080/v1/health"
- Status: ssh jetson@jetson "curl -s http://localhost:8080/v1/status | jq ."

## Development Workflow

1. Edit code locally in services/
2. Test locally if possible (or use cargo check)
3. Build for ARM64 release
4. Sync to Jetson via rsync
5. Restart systemd service on Jetson
6. Test via API endpoints
7. Check logs: ssh jetson@jetson "sudo journalctl -u brain-server -f"